events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Darius Garland collected 23 points and 11 assists, and rookie Evan Mobley had 15 points and a season-high 17 rebounds to power the Cleveland Cavaliers over the Oklahoma City Thunder 94-87 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland, Mobley have big nights, Cavs beat Thunder 94-87

headlines.description: — Devin Booker wound up for a celebratory windmill dunk in the final minute, but misjudged it badly. The ball clanged off the back of the rim and ricocheted downcourt as the home crowd groaned.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges, Biyombo lead Suns to 113-103 win over Pacers
